<p>
Want to get up and running with MinoCloud using PHP? You can either follow the <a href="/docs/(PHP) Quick_App_Tutorial">(PHP) Quick App Tutorial</a> to setup a basic example app to learn from or follow the instructions below to just start using the API.
</p>

<div class="heading">Download <code>minocloud.php</code></div>
<p>
The MinoCloud PHP library can be found <a href="http://minocloud.com/sdk/php/latest.php">here</a>.
</p>

<p>
To <code>Save</code> an <a href="/docs/Items">item</a> that uses a <a href="/docs/Types">type</a> named <code>ExampleUser.Person.1</code> and then <code>Get</code> it, use the following:
</p>

<div class="heading">Save and retrieve an <a href="/docs/Items">item</a></div>
<p>
The following code example shows how to use the <a href="/docs/Save_Function">Save function</a> to save an <a href="/docs/Items">item</a> that uses a <a href="/docs/Types">type</a> named <code>ExampleUser.Person.1</code> and then the <a href="/docs/Get_Function">Get function</a> to retrieve it.
</p>

<p>
This code example uses the PHP convenience functions <a href="/docs/(PHP) save">save</a> and <a href="/docs/(PHP) get">get</a> to call the underlying functions. These convenience functions . These functions act as wrappers for the <a href="/docs/(PHP) api">api</a> function, which can be used to call the MinoCloud <a href="/docs/API">API</a> as per the <a href="/docs/API">API</a> documentation.
</p>

<pre>
&#60;pre&#62;
&#60;?php

  include 'minocloud.php';

  $username = '__YOUR_USERNAME__';
  $api_key = '__YOUR_API_KEY__';

  $minocloud = new MinoCloud($username,$api_key);

  $saveResponse = $minocloud->save(
    array(
      'Name' => 'John Smith',
      'Path' => '/'.$username.'/',
      'ExampleUser.Person.1' => array(
        'First Name' => 'John',
        'Last Name' => 'Smith',
        'Date of Birth' => '1985-05-11'
      )
    )
  );
  echo("Save:\n");
  var_dump($saveResponse);

  $getResponse = $minocloud->get(
    '/'.$username.'/John Smith'
  );

  echo("\nGet:\n");
  var_dump($getResponse);

?&#62;
&#60;/pre&#62;
</pre>

<p>
Output:
</p>

<pre>
Save:
array(7) {
	["Name"]=>
	string(10) "John Smith"
	["Path"]=>
	string(13) "/ExampleUser/"
